line_1: Says the Knight, may I venture to beg a receipt.
line_2: Your haricoes, ma'am, are the best I e'er eat,

line_1: And took, but read not the Receit:
line_2: They paid the Church and Parish-Rate;

line_1: To form some Beauty by a new Receit,
line_2: WHEN Cupid did his Grandsire Jove intreat,

line_1: To transcribe from my grandmother's book a receipt;
line_2: GROWN old, and grown stupid, you just think me fit,
